 igh\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficia
 l Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rat
 e decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n•
  Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bul
 lish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expe
 cted guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.
 \n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interes
 t rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n
 • Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The marke
 t often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement
 \, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federa
 l Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial s
 ource: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-september.htm\n\nE
 xplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: I
 nterest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central b
 ank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is 
 usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovis
 h-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish
  for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly aff
 ect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk ap
 petite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes
 : The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to th
 e statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FO
 MC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\
 nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-septemb
 er.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• 
