 n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for th
 e local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to
  consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early s
 ignal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequenc
 y: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usual
 ly less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation 
 is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\
