 Official source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
 /202610\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measu
 res: Change in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n
 • Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the
  local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to 
 consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early si
 gnal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency
 : Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usuall
 y less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation i
 s the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\n
 Official source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
