 igh\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficia
 l Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n
 • What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rat
 e decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n•
  Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bul
 lish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expe
 cted guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.
 \n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interes
 t rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n
 • Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The marke
 t often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement
 \, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federa
 l Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial s
 ource: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december.htm\n\nEx
 plainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: In
 terest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central ba
 nk.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is u
 sually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish
 -than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish 
 for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affe
 ct interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk app
 etite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes:
  The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the
  statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOM
 C = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\n
 Official source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december
